people already registered</a>, and <a href=\"http://2009.newyork.wordcamp.org/saturday-sessions/\">8 session tracks</a> &#8211; there is something for everyone.</p>\n<p>Myself and several colleagues from Automattic are flying in for this event, and I&#8217;m personally excited to see the track devoted to CMS use featuring case studies of current publishers.</p>\n<p>If you haven&#8217;t <a href=\"http://2009.newyork.wordcamp.org/tickets/\">signed up</a> yet, it&#8217;s $45 for both days, or just $25 for Sunday.  More details available on <a href=\"http://2009.newyork.wordcamp.org/tickets/\">2009.newyork.wordcamp.org</a>.</p>\n<p>[ Visit <a href=\"http://2009.newyork.wordcamp.org/tickets/\">WordCamp NYC 2009</a> and <a href=\"http://central.wordcamp.org/\">WordCamp.org</a> for other WordCamps happening all over the world ]</p>\n  <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wordpresspublishers.wordpress.com/695/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" bor